Healthy snack 

RED KIDNEY BEANS SALAD

 1.Boil overnight soaked kidney bean (rajma) with some salt and let it cool.
2. Do not over boil the beans.
3. Dice onion, capsicum and cucumber.
4. In a mixing bowl add kidney beans, onion, capsicum, cucumber, finely chopped garlic, mixed herbs, red chilli flakes, salt, pepper, lime juice and extra virgin olive oil.
5. Mix well and serve.
Â 

NUTRITIONAL VALUE 

1. Kidney beans are a great source of protein, mineral and vitamins.
2. It is low in cholesterol and is good for diabetics.
3. The good amount of fibre content in kidney beans helps in weight loss.
4. The amount of calcium in kidney beans helps in making bones stronger.

In frame : Penne in pink sauce 
Ratings : 5/5 
Place : Little Italy 

Review : A perfect pasta consists of 3 main things -
1) Perfect cooking of the raw pasta
2) A creamy and flavorful sauce
3)The quality of cheese used in the recipe. 
And Little Italy breaks all bars by setting it standards high by using the perfect amount of flavours and good quality ingredients. 
The pasta's sauce was creamy and tangy, veggies used were fresh and cripsy,and the cheese used was rich. 

Do try the pink sauce pasta next time you visit Little Italy and you will definitely relish the dish.

About pasta : Food historians estimate that the dish probably took hold in Italy as a result of extensive Mediterranean trading in the Middle Ages. From the 13th century, references to pasta dishesâ€”macaroni, ravioli, gnocchi, vermicelliâ€”crop up with increasing frequency across the Italian peninsula. In the 14th-century writer Boccaccioâ€™s collection of earthy tales, The Decameron, he recounts a mouthwatering fantasy concerning a mountain of Parmesan cheese down which pasta chefs roll macaroni and ravioli to gluttons waiting below.

This is such an easy and filling meal that only takes 10 minutes to make if you already have cooked rice in the fridge!! â£
â£
base:â£
jasmine riceâ£
broccoliâ£
tempehâ£
â£
sauce: â£
1 tbsp soy sauceâ£
1 tbsp maple syrupâ£
1/4 tbsp rice vinegarâ£
cornstarch to thicken â£
â£
Start by cooking your rice according to package directions. In the meantime, steam the broccoli and tempeh (tempeh steaming optional). Put the broccoli aside and then cut the tempeh into cubes and use a non-stick pan over medium heat to lightly fry it while making the sauce. Once the tempeh is crisped to your liking, reduce heat to low, and add the broccoli and sauce. Mix this together for a few minutes and then serve over rice.
